  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 4a65c8aaeddc6d14793efeea40a41a91, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  tombolTutup: {fileID: 967126439}
  daftarSlot:
  - namaKunci: Keramik
    containerObject: {fileID: 87170436}
    gambarRempah: {fileID: 83475093}
    sprite: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 0e9bd1aec4178da478b511652f28182b, type: 3}
    namaText: {fileID: 1874472149}
    deskripsiText: {fileID: 74224691}
    nama_ID: Keramik Tiongkok
    nama_EN: Chinese Ceramics
    deskripsi_ID: Keramik dan porselen dari Tiongkok menjadi simbol status bergengsi
      di kalangan bangsawan dan sultan Nusantara.
    deskripsi_EN: Chinese ceramics and porcelain were prestigious status symbols
      among the nobility and sultans of the Nusantara.
  - namaKunci: Beras
    containerObject: {fileID: 732253668}
    gambarRempah: {fileID: 1337230231}
    sprite: {fileID: 21300000, guid: c1ee8be4dc3a9ea498bdbea8f6562f95, type: 3}
    namaText: {fileID: 2098382315}
    deskripsiText: {fileID: 942865049}
    nama_ID: Beras
    nama_EN: Rice
    deskripsi_ID: Beras adalah komoditas logistik paling vital di jalur rempah. Garnisun
      militer VOC di benteng-benteng seperti Benteng Victoria di Ambon sangat bergantung
      pada pasokan beras dari pedagang luar.
    deskripsi_EN: Rice was the most vital logistical commodity along the spice route.
      VOC military garrisons at fortresses such as Fort Victoria in Ambon depended
      heavily on rice supplies from outside traders.
  - namaKunci: Kain
    containerObject: {fileID: 1155797556}
    gambarRempah: {fileID: 1421657350}
    sprite: {fileID: 21300000, guid: caa871cb7e5d2de4f810b110c1a4632d, type: 3}
    namaText: {fileID: 88610238}
    deskripsiText: {fileID: 352131835}
    nama_ID: Kain Patola
    nama_EN: Patola Cloth
    deskripsi_ID: Kain Patola adalah kain sutra bermotif dari Gujarat, India, yang
      memiliki nilai simbolis sangat tinggi di Nusantara. Hanya bangsawan dan raja
      yang berhak mengenakannya dalam upacara adat.
    deskripsi_EN: Patola cloth is a patterned silk fabric from Gujarat, India, that
      held immense symbolic value across the Nusantara. Only nobles and rulers were
      entitled to wear it during traditional ceremonies.
